                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I. Intro
<br />

<br />
Winning ldon high risk isnt impossible for a 4kish hp buffed enchanter, but you had better form a group that will keep you out of harms way for the most part. Ive tried to write this guide from the perspective of a typical enchanter with pre elemental gear. When I first started doing ldon high risk (with about 4300hps depending on who was in the group) I died a LOT but after some hard lessons I got the hang of it. Now Im rocking high risk and I figured some ppl out there could benefit from what I had to learn the hard way.
<br />

<br />
II. Group Make Up
<br />

<br />
Ideally a 4kish hp enc should form the high risk group himself, that way he can ensure that the group will have a good chance to win. Heres what you want in a group:
<br />

<br />
1.Puller (PAL, BARD, MNK)
<br />

<br />
2.Primary Slower (BST is your best choice here because they have decent DPS but a SHM will work too)
<br />

<br />
3.Healer (CLR ONLY)
<br />

<br />
4.Tank (WAR PAL...maybe a really good SK, look for 9k+ hps)
<br />

<br />
5.CC/DPS (thats you man! learn to love charm if you havent already because in many cases charming is the only way you have a shot at winning)
<br />

<br />
6.Open Slot (I almost always fill this with a DPS toon like Wizard or rogue, but if you have a druid friend you feel sorry for you can let him in and pray you get a pet early on)
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is the typical group I get. Im not saying im the best at LDoN high risk, but I do have the most high risk wins on Fennin for enchanters (3rd place overall).
<br />

<br />
Can you do it with other group make ups? Sure anything is possible but I like to stack the odds in my favor if I can.
<br />

<br />

<br />
But it takes soooo long to get the necessary people...I cant wait that long. Then do normal risk. If you dont have the patience to form a winning group in high risk then you prolly arent ready for it.
<br />

<br />
III. Risk vs Reward
<br />

<br />
Is the risk worth the reward? I think so. I am elemental flagged but I never got my VT key, thus I had some really nice gear and some really crappy gear (just got rid of a Bracer of Beauty for ele bracer last nite uhg). 
<br />

<br />
With high risk I was able to get a LOT of really nice upgrades that are just below VT quality. Most items have 90 hps/mana and a decent effect combined with other stats and resists of course. Not to mention the decent exp (approx 1 aa per mission) and Adventure Points.
<br />

<br />
Early on when LDoN came out, me and a tracker and healer and tank would get high risk mission, zone in to check for close by rares, kill them and then leave. In this way we got a bunch of nice equipment. A lot fo it was droppable too. Sure I racked up about 12 losses on my record this way but I dont care.
<br />

<br />
IV. Spell Line Up
<br />

<br />
Heres is my LDoN High Risk spell set:
<br />

<br />
1. Arcane Rune
<br />
2. Scryer's Tresspass
<br />
3. Command of Druzzil
<br />
4. Rune of Zeb
<br />
5. Tash
<br />
6. Word of Morell
<br />
7. Color Cloud
<br />
8. Bliss (duh)
<br />

<br />
Spell Line up Notes:
<br />

<br />
Youre going to want to get Color Cloud asap. Not because its vastly superior to WoM, but because it gives you TWO stuns. Whether you use it as back up or primary is up to you, but either way youre going to want this spell asap.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Keep yourself double runed at all times if you have a pet. This will save your ass! 
<br />

<br />
But root isnt in my line up!!! 
<br />
Well you cant root your pet in ldon. If I had 9 spell gems root would be in the 9th. Therse a nice shield with right click immobilize from PoAir that rocks if you can get your hands on one. Short of that, the only spell that could be considered optional imo is rune of Zeb, and if i had to choose between the two for this situation im going with an extra 1500hps that may give the slow fingered cleric enough time to get a heal off. 
<br />

<br />
Maybe scryers could go drop out too, but i think the spell is a lot more useful than root in ldon high risk because there are a lot of casters and when charming, mana can become an issue. Especially for an enchanter with 4k hps cuz they prolly dont have the greatest mana pool or regen either.
<br />

<br />
OMG you dont have slow memmed! 
<br />
Thats right. the Beast/shammy will be the all time slower, with 4khps that last thing you need is more aggro / mana consuming spells.
<br />

<br />

<br />
V. Pulling in LDoN High Risk:
<br />

<br />
 If you are a 4kish hp enc, dont do it. In normal risk you can slow pull mez and charm np. This is NOT the case in high risk. Pacification is resisted a LOT more in high risk. With 260 cha its common to get aggro from pacify, with 305 you are pretty much safe from aggro but pacify will still drain your mana fast with all the resists. Even now with over 6k hps I dont mess around with pulling. Occasionally I will have to break up a room with pacify, but this should be your groups back up plan. Pacify is a tool, not a crutch.
<br />

<br />
There a few differences in the pulling styles of the various classes. Personally I prefer a good pally with a lot of hps because in a pinch he can double as MT with np. Plus a good pally can be your guardian angel, stunning on recharm and healing your ass with LoH. Pally pullers can get you some fairly large pulls tho so you have to be ready.
<br />

<br />
The good news about pally pulls is that at very least the inc mobs are staggered a bit, that way you have time for spell to refresh, target and mez. Hope for the best but prepare for the worst. Get a pally that will comminucate with you. Have him tell you when the pull could go bad, or ask for a pacify. 
<br />

<br />
After the bards lull nerf you will typically see bards pull 1-2 mobs each pull. Np at all here imo. It used to be damn near garunteed single pulls every time. Bard can help you recharm and mez and in general are pretty cool if you can find one that will join you.
<br />

<br />
Monks can pull ldon high risk too, they are usually my last choice however. Not because they cant get singles but because it take them longer to split a room than the other 2 types of pullers. Time is a factor so if you get a monk make sure he has a lot of hps and isnt afriad to pull 2-3 when you have to hurry.
<br />

<br />

<br />
VI.Reasons I die in LDoN High Risk
<br />

<br />
1. Get aggro from a mez resist and then charm breaks. 
<br />

<br />
If you are tanking 2 mobs while trying to channel a stun or mez whatever you are going to need help from someone, be it heals from the cleric or stuns from the pally. With out help, my chances of dying are high. If im grouped with a some ppl I dont know very well I tend to send the pally a tell saying, "help me out on charm breaks with stuns and heal" or something to that effect. Bards can help a TON on charm breaks, most good one will have a "Save the Enchnater from becomming a smear on the floor" hotkey that will mez whatever you have targetted. 
<br />

<br />
2. Bad decisions combined with bad luck.
<br />

<br />
Every get a 2 pull and you mez the target the tanks are fighting? Of course you have it happens all the time. Sometimes this will draw aggrro and you get beat on while your gems are refreshing, then all of a sudden you get low hp aggro and both of them are on you and youre gib. Moral of the story here is be extra careful, with 4kish hp you dont have room for too many mistakes.
<br />

<br />
3. Things beyond my control.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes even the best pullers can get too many and die as they hit camp. Sometimes cleric can be day dreaming for a sec while you are recharming and you die. SOme times you ae stun and set of a trap that dots your pet making it impossible to mez him for a recharm. 
<br />

<br />
VII. Mission Types
<br />

<br />
What type of missions should i choose?
<br />

<br />
Good question. Assuming no one is cheating, get low collects (23 or less) or low slaughters if you have a group with exceptional DPS. If you have good maps GET rescue! If you have a cheater in the group definately get rescue. I would avoid assassinate in high risk alltogether because its just too unpredictable.
<br />

<br />
It all breaks down to luck in this area BUT the smart enc will select a mission type based on whether or not the group is high DPS or more defensive in nature.
<br />

<br />
VIII. AAs
<br />

<br />
Recommended AAs in order of PRIORITY:
<br />

<br />
[Eldritch Rune 3] 
<br />
[Gather Mana] 
<br />
[Hastened Gathering 3] 
<br />
[Defensive AAs]
<br />
[PLanar Power, get that cha MAXED int too]
<br />

<br />
IX. Final Thought (Jerry Springer style):
<br />

<br />
One thing I didnt mention is that YOU have to be a GOOD enchanter. We all know that gear does not make a good enchanter, its just a cusion. To succeed here you have to to be on the ball at ALL times, mezzing ASAP, and controlling your pet. DOnt be afraid to mez your pet and keep him on ice for a bit while you lock down a large pull. EXPECT charm to break the the WORST times. It will trust me, but at least if you are always looking for it, you wont be surprised. 
<br />

<br />
Threat analysis is a CRITICAL skill for enchanters. When mobs are inc you need to be very good at making split second descsions on what to mez. The cleric cant take much more of a hit than you, and when 3-4 mobs inc, the cleric is bound to draw aggro from at least 1. Expect this. 
<br />

<br />
In general your priorities should be.
<br />

<br />
1. Mez mobs attacking me
<br />
2. Mez mobs attacking cleric
<br />
3. Mez mobs attacking slower/tanks.
<br />
4. Recharm
<br />
5. Refresh runes. (enchanter with out protection is a threat just not a direct one)
<br />

<br />
Notice how recharm is at the bottom of the list? Ive lost a few clerics because I was stunning then recharming an ex pet while they were tanking a mob. In a jam just mez it and deal with it later. Youre going to want to mez it fairly regularly anyways to refresh tash and malo if available.
<br />

<br />
LDoN high risk can be very fun and very frustrating, but it provides the only challenging dungeon available for a good lvl 65 enchanter. At first you may hate high risk, but eventually you will become like me and LOVE them. Through ldon loot alone I raised my hps 800-1k at least. Throw in some elemental loot here and that and boom you have 6k hps in a few months! 
<br />

<br />
I take pride in the fact that I have more high wins than any timeflagged enchanters on Fennin. with a few wins under your belt you will be proud of what you accomplished too. GL and Have fun I hope this guide was useful to someone. Feel free to reply if you think im wrong about something, I like to discuss way to get better <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://strike9.com/file.ashx?path=%2fVizier%2ffullsize%2fVizierSig4.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
One name...many faces.
<br />
-Vizier, 65 Coercer of Fennin Ro</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Vizier on Sat Jan 03, 2004 11:05 am; edited 3 times in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
