		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><a name="15769"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Vizier</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_7.gif" alt="Coercer" title="Coercer" border="0" /><br />Coercer</div><div align="center"><img src="images/avatars/6961508773fa91cd697603.jpg" alt="Avatar" border="0" /></div><br /><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;24 Sep 2003</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;214</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Location:&nbsp;Washington DC</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Male</div></td>
                <td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=15769&amp;sid=8fbca26122f6cf1b52f368aa36fc1dc8#15769"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Sat Jan 03, 2004 10:47 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=15769&amp;sid=8fbca26122f6cf1b52f368aa36fc1dc8"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">You say that gear does not make the character, you have to be good. I agree... but to be good you have to know where the margins are, what you can get away with. For that, I need to know the same lessons you got from all your deaths... why/when were you dying and what did you change because of it? That's the info I need for good threat analysis and split second decisions. Even if your style matched my style completely, I'd still need to be able to make small adjustments to your (very good) guide based on the group I'm with. 
<br />

<br />
Were you dying because you tried to pull? Or because you hasted your pet and it chewed you up? Maybe you tried to do slow and CC at the same time and either ran low on mana or suffered some dead clerics. Or maybe you just learned that rune was more important than root. Did you have different problems with a paladin puller than with a monk puller? Does it help to have an evaccer with an itchy trigger finger? 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
-Definately died a lot less once I started using the 2nd rune instead of root.
<br />
-If you want to fill your DPS slot with a wizard its all good imo. Evac has saved the mission single handedly many times. Keep your options open.
<br />
- I also updated the final thought to include some more info on threat analysis.
<br />

<br />
Reasons I die in LDoN High RIsk
<br />

<br />
1. Get aggro from a mez resist and then charm breaks. 
<br />

<br />
If you are tanking 2 mobs while trying to channel a stun or mez whatever you are going to need help from someone, be it heals from the cleric or stuns from the pally. With out help, my chances of dying are high. If im grouped with a some ppl I dont know very well I tend to send the pally a tell saying, "help me out on charm breaks with stuns and heal" or something to that effect. Bards can help a TON on charm breaks, most good one will have a "Save the Enchnater from becomming a smear on the floor" hotkey that will mez whatever you have targetted. 
<br />

<br />
2. Bad decisions combined with bad luck.
<br />

<br />
Every get a 2 pull and you mez the target the tanks are fighting? Of course you have it happens all the time. Sometimes this will draw aggrro and you get beat on while your gems are refreshing, then all of a sudden you get low hp aggro and both of them are on you and youre gib. Moral of the story here is be extra careful, with 4kish hp you dont have room for too many mistakes.
<br />

<br />
3. Things beyond my control.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes even the best pullers can get too many and die as they hit camp. Sometimes cleric can be day dreaming for a sec while you are recharming and you die. SOme times you ae stun and set of a trap that dots your pet making it impossible to mez him for a recharm. 
<br />

<br />
Pulling in LDoN High Risk:
<br />

<br />
Dont do it. In normal risk you can slow pull mez and charm np. This is NOT the case in high risk. Pacification is resisted a LOT more in high risk. With 260 cha its common to get aggro from pacify, with 305 you are pretty much safe from aggro but pacify will still drain your mana fast with all the resists. Even now with over 6k hps I dont mess around with pulling. Occasionally I will have to break up a room with pacify, but this should be your groups back up plan. Pacify is a tool, not a crutch.
<br />

<br />
There a few differences in the pulling styles of the various classes. Personally I prefer a good pally with a lot of hps because in a pinch he can double as MT with np. Plus a good pally can be your guardian angel, stunning on recharm and healing your ass with LoH. Pally pullers can get you some fairly large pulls tho so you have to be ready.
<br />

<br />
The good news about pally pulls is that at very least the inc mobs are staggered a bit, that way you have time for spell to refresh, target and mez. Hope for the best but prepare for the worst. Get a pally that will comminucate with you. Have him tell you when the pull could go bad, or ask for a pacify. 
<br />

<br />
After the bards lull nerf you will typically see bards pull 1-2 mobs each pull. Np at all here imo. It used to be damn near garunteed single pulls every time. Bard can help you recharm and mez and in general are pretty cool if you can find one that will join you.
<br />

<br />
Monks can pull ldon high risk too, they are usually my last choice however. Not because they cant get singles but because it take them longer to split a room than the other 2 types of pullers. Time is a factor so if you get a monk make sure he has a lot of hps and isnt afraid to pull 2-3 when you have to hurry.
<br />

<br />
----
<br />

<br />
I think ill add this post to the actual guide. Whoever wanted to use this on a different site plz go ahead. I hope ppl can find some useful info here and give ldon high risk a shot.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
