                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have to agree with not pulling at hard difficulty. Counting on the pet to hold off mobs while you sort them all is risky business if you get a break on incoming, which happened frequently when I tried my hand at it.
<br />

<br />
I pulled once in a weak group for the whole mission - and we lost. Haven't pulled in the rest of the ~100 or so other hard missions I did except on a sporadic basis when the rest of the group is becoming comatose for some reason. I had a bard to pull once, and a monk maybe 7-8 times... we usually just have the tank pull and I mez adds. The good old fashioned way <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> no reason it can't work well with communication and some people helping with root, even with tanks with "supbar" gear, meaning with 6.5K - 7.5K hps. It is a lot easier with a 10K hps warrior of course, but I don't wait for one to be available to get a group going. 
<br />

<br />
I'd say even a wizard is as good a choice to pull. They have snare and greater fetter and can split mobs on inc pretty well given room to move, and the group can handle the loss of the wizard a lot better than it can the loss of the enchanter.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
