                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I personally pull most of the time in Hard (seem to only do hard advent's), granted I've got the luxury of time level gear. But in most cases mezz pulling is one of the single greatest pulling tools at our disposal (bards split alot w/ mezz as well because of this reason). Bliss is very rarely resisted in hard. One thing I allways do is make sure I have Illusion: Scaled Wolf (SoW or whatever just make sure your fast.) up, turning your average 3 pull into 1 is easy as pie. Just make sure you have alot of room, to pull.
<br />

<br />
Mezz generates a smaller aggro radius than most spells like tash or slow so alot of times you can get that one mob off in the corner to not come when using on of those spells. Get 2 of the 3 mobs you want to controll on target use your fast switch key to toggle between the two of them. Mezz the first, switch targets using the hotkey, while running back to the group. Root the other one befor it even gets a chance to come close to the group. Now you still have 1 inc, well it's only proxy aggroed on you atm so if you run past your tank, and he's not a compleat moron, he'll attack it and it'll instantly aggro him. You can then mezz the rooted one, move up root the first one you mezzed and take your time killing.
<br />

<br />
I also generally don't do alot of charming, if I can I will I just don't go out of my way to do so. Espec if I'm pulling.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=173508" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/ryoga179/myhomepage/newdredsig.jpg?mtbrand=AOL_US]" border="0" /></a>
