                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well let me clarify a bit:
<br />

<br />
When youre first starting out and trying to learn how to be successful in high risk, its prolly not the best idea to try pulling right away. Take it slow and get your feet wet is the best strat imo.
<br />

<br />
If you have 4k hps, you prolly dont have a huge mana pool or more than ft7 or so. Keeping a pet is going to be a drain on your mana pool, keep that in mind.
<br />

<br />
Can enchanters pull in high risk? sure like I said anything is possible. I have elemental gear and i usually dont pull becasue I form groups that make enchanter pulling unecessary. These type of groups have a higher probablility for winning in my experience, and that what this guide is made for...tips that can give the inexperinced enchanter the edge they need to win.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://strike9.com/file.ashx?path=%2fVizier%2ffullsize%2fVizierSig4.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
One name...many faces.
<br />
-Vizier, 65 Coercer of Fennin Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
